      <intermediateExchange id="28fb6190-fda1-582b-8ee2-1f1f6d69d1c6" unitId="241450a3-3497-4648-8c68-e44d04f64ac7" amount="0.0177777777777778" isCalculatedAmount="true" mathematicalRelation="((transport_lorry_RM+transport_lorry_reefer)/ speed_lorry)*1000/24* fraction_time_reefer_transfer" intermediateExchangeId="12beeeef-5f97-45c3-89ae-6174be37eb41" activityLinkId="fc39db3f-1e80-5f45-a41c-45e69065b222">
        <name xml:lang="en">operation, reefer, cooling</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg*day</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Calculated value extrapolated from other GLO markets for crops.
Original comment: The reefer operates (is cooling or freezing down the goods) no matter if it is being transported or if it is standing in a port or farm and not moving. The amount of operation of reefer needed is connected directly to different modes of transport using default assumptions on the average speed of the infrastructure.
This exchange represents the time, when the reefer is being transferred from one mode of the transport to another. So for example the reefer is taken by a truck to the port, where it is transferred to a transoceanic ship. During this time the transport vehicles are not moving, but the reefer keeps operating and maintaining the required atmosphere.
Based on an estimate 20% of amount of operation, reefer, cooling is added to cover the time when the reefer is transferred between different types of transport.  So, for example, if the goods stay and is being transported by the different modes of transport for 10 days there are 2 more days added that represent the time when the reefer is being transferred from the truck to the ship and from the ship to the train, etc.</comment>
        <uncertainty>
          <lognormal meanValue="0.0177777777777778" mu="-4.0298060410845284" variance="0.0006" varianceWithPedigreeUncertainty="0.0506"/>
          <pedigreeMatrix reliability="1" completeness="1" temporalCorrelation="4" geographicalCorrelation="5" furtherTechnologyCorrelation="4"/>
        </uncertainty>
        <property propertyId="f2283db2-62e4-467f-b9ac-c4f45be563b4" amount="0.0" isDefiningValue="false" isCalculatedAmount="false" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7">
