      <intermediateExchange id="8554ac36-ed75-537b-bbe4-4641ce354163" unitId="2f4daad7-5331-4f14-930c-d8bca924557d" variableName="transport_lorry_reefer" amount="0.0864" isCalculatedAmount="true" mathematicalRelation="96/1000*0.9" intermediateExchangeId="3d793ffb-b1ef-42e3-a3ac-6894faf26264" activityLinkId="4e20438e-3e6e-525c-932e-8b622ac12c97">
        <name xml:lang="en">transport, freight, lorry with reefer, cooling</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">metric ton*km</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Sweet corn is transported on average 96 km by lorry (100%) in the US. Data from 2006. It is assumed that the sweet corn is transported with refrigeration, since sweet corn is a highly perishable crop. When produced for commercial markets, it must be cooled immediately and thoroughly after harvest to protect its quality. It must be kept cool until it reaches the consumer.
The share between the types of lorry was extrapolated from other GLO markets of crops. Original comment: "It is estimated (based on production volumes), that 90% of the transport by lorry is by big lorries which carry a reefer and 10% by small lorries with build in refrigeration machine".
References:
Jean Miller Melissa. Cradle to Consumer Life Cycle Greenhouse Gas Accounting of Sweet Corn in Minnesota. FACULTY OF THE UNIVERSITY OF MINNESOTA. 2017
https://conservancy.umn.edu/bitstream/handle/11299/191252/Miller_umn_0130M_18041.pdf?sequence=1
https://content.ces.ncsu.edu/postharvest-cooling-and-handling-of-sweet-corn 
https://usatruckloadshipping.com/how-to-ship-georgia-sweet-corn/
https://usatruckloadshipping.com/how-is-corn-packaged-and-shipped/
https://www.vegetables.bayer.com/nz/en-nz/resources/growing-tips/agronomic-spotlights/postharvest-sweet-corn-handling-and-storage.html#:~:text=To%20continue%20to%20help%20maintain,moisture%20loss%20and%20maintain%20temperature.&amp;text=The%20recommended%20temperature%20during%20transit,between%2095%25%20to%2098%25.</comment>
        <uncertainty>
          <lognormal meanValue="0.0864" mu="-2.448767603172127" variance="0.12" varianceWithPedigreeUncertainty="0.161225"/>
