        <comment xml:lang="en">Value extrapolated from "market for potato / GLO", accessed on 20230809. Original comment: Estimated value.</comment>
      </parameter>
      <parameter parameterId="67d91564-dd27-4166-9796-689b78ff86ff" amount="0.12" variableName="losses" unitId="577e242a-461f-44a7-922c-d8e1c3d2bf45">
        <name xml:lang="en">losses</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">dimensionless</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Value extrapolated from "market for potato / GLO", accessed on 20230908. 
Original comment:
Calculated value based on literature.
FAO suggest, that 1/3 of food produced for human consumption is lost or waste globally, which amounts in 1.3 billion tons per year (FAO, 2011, Global food losses and food waste).
The food losses vary heavily depending on the type of food and geographic location. The food losses/waste occurs in five basic stages of the lifecycle of the product;
1) Agricultural production
2) Post-harvest handling and storage
3) Processing
4) Distribution
5) Consumption

The losses during the forth stage - the distribution - are recorded in the market.

Literature suggest (FAO, 2011, Global food losses and food waste), that the losses of fruits and vegetable distribution are approximately 12%. This value is rather rough estimate and it is assumed, that in the future this value will be replaced by more precise, product specific data.</comment>
      </parameter>
      <parameter parameterId="3819b90e-0c78-4ad8-9cf9-58b415446628" amount="45.0" variableName="speed_lorry" unitId="33964fe2-6f44-4ed6-844d-b29dea69aad0">
        <name xml:lang="en">speed, average, lorry, freight</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">km/hour</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Value extrapolated from "market for potato / GLO", accessed on 20230908. 
Original comments: 
Expert judgement.
Average velocity including stops.
Reference: 45 km/hour is the default speed of lorries and trucks used to calculate delivery distances  (www.searates.com, accessed 20141201).</comment>
      </parameter>
